Welcome to the show! Today we are going to talk about the popular beauty and fashion influencer, Tana Marie, who has recently been in the news for a controversial beauty product. We will discuss the controversy and the lore surrounding Tana Marie.

We start by discussing the controversy surrounding Tana Marie's beauty product, which has been criticized for its lack of effectiveness and for being overpriced. Some people have also accused Tana Marie of using her influence to promote the product and deceive her followers.

We then move on to the lore surrounding Tana Marie. One interesting lore is that Tana Marie is a descendant of the famous comedian, George Carlin. Another lore is that Tana Marie has a secret love for the TV show, Friends.

We also discuss the popular beauty and fashion influencers, such as Kylie Jenner and Selena Gomez, and their influence on the beauty industry. We also touch on the topic of influencer marketing and how brands use influencers to promote their products.

Overall, this episode was filled with interesting discussions and insights into the world of beauty and fashion influencers. We hope you enjoyed listening!

The Cancelled Podcast is a satirical podcast that makes fun of social media influencers and their fake lives. In this episode, the hosts, Brooke and Tana, discuss various topics related to social media influencers, such as sponsored trips, the importance of engagement, and the pressure to always look perfect. They also discuss various scandals and controversies related to influencers, such as the Selena Gomez-Taylor Swift feud and the Kylie Jenner lip kit scandal. The episode is filled with humor and satire, and the hosts often make fun of themselves and their own fake lives. The episode ends with a discussion on the upcoming tour and the possibility of a collaboration with a famous artist.
